build.gradle file will be redundant if PR #2143 gets merged and in that case , I will remove it from this PR

pr_review_comments: [{'comment_id': 1198519395, 'comment_body': 'IDE automatically added Kotlin Synthetic library due to some workaround. We need to get rid of this. ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 5, 19, 4, 0, 30, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gururani-abhishek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1198522503, 'comment_body': 'The workaround that introduced above Kotlin synthetic lib is here. "toolbar" is the name of layout, not it's ID, hence when you're accessing it using "binding.root.toolbar" Kotlin Synthetic is getting used, what we can do instead is : 1. in HomeActivity.xml give the included layout "toolbar" some id 2. then access it using that ID, something like this -> binding.idGivenToToolbar.root(do double-check on this, I'm not 100% sure) this type of workaround is expected with included layouts read more here -> [Stackoverflow](https://stackoverflow.com/a/58730128)', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 5, 19, 4, 8, 28, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gururani-abhishek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1198527043, 'comment_body': "This works perfectly fine but just a suggestion -> Instead of calling setSupportActionBar() right from our activities, how bout overriding setContentView(view : View?) {...setSupportActionBar()...} in our BaseActivity()?[ reference](https://github.com/openMF/mifos-mobile/pull/2143/commits/ea586368a7cb09fc982260606f0a6fc8ceeb9169#diff-061eaf0e6e045746e15221e289cc4e5623af2fa6e9e66c12818794c97a48a10b) This way we can save ourselves from writing extra code, plus similar feature was already there in BaseActivity() while we were using Butterknife. Still it's just a suggestion, totally your call.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 5, 19, 4, 19, 35, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gururani-abhishek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1198530473, 'comment_body': 'Why are we showing a backButton in HomeActivity? It'll overlap navigation drawer icon with the backButton. ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 5, 19, 4, 27, 10, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gururani-abhishek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1198542510, 'comment_body': 'Please remove this unused import.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 5, 19, 4, 54, 7, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gururani-abhishek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1198543539, 'comment_body': '"nsv_background" is being accessed using Kotlin Synthetic, use binding here. And remove Kotlin Synthetic Library from the imports too.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 5, 19, 4, 56, 20, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gururani-abhishek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1198545458, 'comment_body': 'remove this unused import please', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 5, 19, 5, 0, 22, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gururani-abhishek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1198553953, 'comment_body': 'Use of ButterKnife!! replace it with ViewBinding please. pr_title: fix : migrating fragments from butterknife to viewbinding
pr_body:
Fixes #2142 

This PR lists the fragments that have been migrated to viewbinding :  
- LocationFragment
- TransferProcessFragment
- RecentTransactionsFragment
- QrCodeReaderFragment
- ThirdPartyTransferFragment
- QrCodeImportFragment
- QrCodeDisplayFragment
pr_review_comments: [{'comment_id': 1204834831, 'comment_body': 'Why are we declaring a whole binding variable for accessing the included error_layout? ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 5, 24, 22, 59, 36, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gururani-abhishek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1204835820, 'comment_body': 'We can access this using binding.layoutError.btnTryAgain(do a cross check). I think using a separate errorLayoutBinding variable is not required. ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 5, 24, 23, 1, 35, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gururani-abhishek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1204837094, 'comment_body': 'Also in the terms of context referencing "btnTryAgain" using errorLayoutBinding will be different than using binding. layoutError.btnTryAgain', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 5, 24, 23, 4, 1, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gururani-abhishek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1204849389, 'comment_body': 'check the review left in ThirdPartyTransferFragment.kt regarding errorLayoutBinding and please make the necessary changes. ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 5, 24, 23, 27, 18, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gururani-abhishek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1204850600, 'comment_body': 'A better way to put this up would be inside onViewCreated() because according to the lifecycle, onViewCreated() confirms that the view is created and now we can interact with the view elements. ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 5, 24, 23, 30, 7, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gururani-abhishek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1204851672, 'comment_body': 'We can put all of these view interactions(listeners) inside onViewCreated() this way we can be sure that the view has already been created and now we can interact with the individual view elements. ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 5, 24, 23, 32, 31, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gururani-abhishek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1205064081, 'comment_body': '`R.id.btn_try_again` was defined in the `error_layout.xml` file and I thought using the appropriate binding object would make more sense.\r\n', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 5, 25, 6, 44, 54, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'PratyushSingh07', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1205064455, 'comment_body': 'True that , I will try this and let you know\r\n', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 5, 25, 6, 45, 17, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'PratyushSingh07', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1205248218, 'comment_body': 'We are using "binding.root" twice, it\'ll be a great for the purpose of clean coding if we create a val rootView = binding.root, and use it wherever Root View is required. Just a suggestion, totally your call. ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 5, 25, 9, 25, 48, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gururani-abhishek', 'type': 'User'}]

  enum class AboutUsListItemId{
        OfficialWebsite,
        PrivacyPolicy,
        ...

Then use this this as a param in `AboutUsItem` data class:

    val itemId: AboutUsListItemId
)
